summary: Bill Fanter provides watchlist for September 15th week ahead of FOMC rate decision. He discusses bearish setups on ORCL, TSLA, CBRL, FDX, and LULU while highlighting key support levels on NVDA (177) and potential turnaround on NKE. He emphasizes market is fully valued despite pricing in rate cuts, and warns of tariff impacts on small companies and retailers. Not trading Wednesday morning due to FOMC, hosting webinar on fake outs vs breakouts instead.
